org.apache.uima.wikipedia.cr.factory
Class MWArticleFactory

java.lang.Object
  org.apache.uima.wikipedia.cr.factory.MWArticleFactory

public class MWArticleFactory
extends Object

This class is a factory for the articles. It is used for two main purposes :

The first goal was to extract the processing of the string the parser gives us out of the parser itself, thus making the parsers code much more readable. It also makes the parser's code more robust, since you don't have to dig into it when you find the need to modify how you handle the titles for example.

The second goal was to allow the building of articles as immutable objects. This way, we can make the MWArticle object's fields public, thus avoiding the needs of verbose getters to access the data, while making sure the state of the object remains untouched.

Only a subset of the data available in the XML files we process is considered. For more information on this you should read the wiki.

Author:
Maxime Bury <Maxime.bury@gmail.com>

Constructor Detail

MWArticleFactory

public MWArticleFactory(MWSiteinfo siteinfo)
Default initialisation of the fields. The title is set to the empty string, the namespace is set to 0 (default namespace), the id is set to -1 and the revision list is initialized (empty).

newInstance

Get the current article.

Returns:
a new instance of MWArticle as crafted by the factory.

hasTitle

public final void hasTitle(String prefixedTitle)
Sets the title and namespace of the article the factory is currently crafting. The namespace is stored as an integer which is the key to the corresponding name in the MWSiteInfo object. In order to get an accurate namespace index, we rely on the fact that the parser managed to gather the website info correctly. If that's not the case, we just assume the article is in the default (0) namespace.

Parameters:
prefixedTitle - the article's title

hasId

public final void hasId(String id)
Sets the id of the article the factory is currently crafting. It gets a String from the parser and tries to turn it into an integer. If it fails, the default value is -1.

Parameters:
id - the revision's id.

Parameters:
